CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 23, 1946, pg. 12, reads: "Fish Story - This ten-pound fish was lined in Allegheny River near Grove, Pa., by alert followers of Isaac Walton. The fishermen were Bob Williams, Floyd Skil[es], Tom Williams, and Bob Evans.  The fish was thirty inches long. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Bob Williams, Floyd Skiles, Tom Williams, and Bob Evans standing in street holding large fish
